wikipedia_page.main: Lily Isabelle Owsley,  (born 10 December 1994) in Bristol, England is an English field hockey player who plays as a midfielder or forward for Dutch club hdm and the England and Great Britain national teams.

response: Whilst still studying at the university, student Lily Owsley scored the gold medal-winning goal at the 2016 Rio Olympics with the help of teammate and fellow UoB graduate Sophie Bray.
